message.content: cs.IT, cs.IT is the most likely category as the paper deals with information theory and coding performance. Other likely categories could be cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) as the paper discusses approximation formulas, cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) as the paper deals with decoding rules, cs.NA (numerical analysis) as the paper discusses Taylor-type expansion, and cs.SY (systems and control) as the paper discusses optimal codeword symbol distribution.
